# ShowUp — Backend

## Layout

- Routes: `server/router/{domain}Routes.js` → register in `server/app.js` under `/api/v1/...`
- Controllers: named exports wrapped with `catchAsyncError`
- Tables: `server/models/*Table.js` → register in `server/utils/createTables.js`
- DB access: parameterized SQL only via `server/database/db.js`

## API

- Success: `{ success: true, ...data }`
- Validation/errors: `return next(new ErrorHandler(message, statusCode))`
- Auth stacks: `isAuthenticated`, `authorizedRoles('admin'|'user')`, `optionalAuth` on public reads that need user context
- Request JSON: camelCase; DB columns: snake_case; strip secrets with `sanitizeUser()` before returning users

## Conventions

- ES modules (`import`/`export`); `async/await` only
- Project moderation lives on `/api/v1/projects`; admin router is users, categories, dashboard
- GitHub: validate repo URLs before API calls; `GITHUB_TOKEN` server-side only
- Add `@openapi` comments when other routes in the same router file use them
